Nigeria Labour Congress says it will not go back on proposed plans to protest unpaid entitlement of workers in Ogun. Labour president Ayuba Wabba insisted at a briefing in Abeokuta that the strike tagged “Operation Occupy Ogun State” will go on as planned on Tuesday. “Nobody has monopoly of threats,” he said at a briefing at Labour’s secretariat in Abeokuta, the state capital. Governor Ibikunle Amosun had threatened Labour leaders to steer clear of Ogun amidst the planned protest. Unpaid entitlements: We’ll lock down Ogun Friday – NLC president Wabba to lead 'Occupy Ogun' protest over workers' plight We must rescue Ogun workers from Amosun — NLC President